(67, 1, 77, 'Stage 2 Daily Diary', 'Stage 2 Daily Diary', 'Stage 2 Daily Diary', 'User Evaluation of an Obstacle Alerting System\r\nDaily Dairy\r\n\r\nPlease can you and/or your carer complete this daily diary for the two monitoring periods. The periods may be up to 7 days each and will be agreed when the Obstacle Alerting System [OAS] is fitted.\r\nThe first period will be with the OAS on and the second with the OAS off.\r\nThe information recorded in the diary will include: Your feedback on the OAS, when and where you are driving your powered wheelchair (PWC), how you are feeling and what medication you have taken. \r\nEach day will be roughly divided into:\r\nMorning = Getting up to Lunch time.\r\nAfternoon = Lunch time to tea/supper.\r\nEvening=suppertime to going to bed. \r\nNight=going to bed to getting up.', 'User Evaluation of an Obstacle Alerting System\r\nDaily Dairy\r\n\r\nPlease can you and/or your carer complete this daily diary for the two monitoring periods. The periods may be up to 7 days each and will be agreed when the Obstacle Alerting System [OAS] is fitted.\r\nThe first period will be with the OAS on and the second with the OAS off.\r\nThe information recorded in the diary will include: Your feedback on the OAS, when and where you are driving your powered wheelchair (PWC), how you are feeling and what medication you have taken. \r\nEach day will be roughly divided into:\r\nMorning = Getting up to Lunch time.\r\nAfternoon = Lunch time to tea/supper.\r\nEvening=suppertime to going to bed. \r\nNight=going to bed to getting up.', 'User Evaluation of an Obstacle Alerting System\r\nDaily Dairy\r\n\r\nPlease can you and/or your carer complete this daily diary for the two monitoring periods. The periods may be up to 7 days each and will be agreed when the Obstacle Alerting System [OAS] is fitted.\r\nThe first period will be with the OAS on and the second with the OAS off.\r\nThe information recorded in the diary will include: Your feedback on the OAS, w